This paper deals with the problem of finding hidden structures in large data matrices, which is a fundamental problem in computer science and statistics. The paper uses techniques from computational complexity theory, graph theory, and probability theory to establish lower bounds for the Sum of Squares (SOS) semidefinite hierarchy. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CC (Computational Complexity), followed by cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), cs.IT (Information Theory), cs.LG (Machine Learning), and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
